  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to explore the connection between gait variability parameters
      and balance performance in children with physical disability
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Step length and step time variability will be measured with an electronic walkway, strength
      of 4 lower-extremity muscle groups will be tested bilaterally with a hand held dynamometer,
      walking performance as will be assessed by the 2 minute walk test, energy expenditure index
      (EEI) and rating of perceived exertion (OMNI scale).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
